author: Nick O'Malley | nomalley@masslive.com
title: Prince Fielder falls over fence during celebration as Texas Rangers win in 15 innings
text:
Prince Fielder falls over fence during celebration as Texas Rangers win in 15 innings Prince Fielder The Texas Rangers won the game, but it was a rough ending for Prince Fielder. (AP Photo/LM Otero) Comments 
The Texas Rangers-Toronto Blue Jays ALDS Game 2 had a nice early starting time, but it sure didn't end early. The two teams slogged through a 14-inning affair before the Rangers finally put it to bed by putting two runs across in the top of the final inning. 
You'll have to excuse the two teams if they were a little tired. Well, everyone except Prince Fielder. The Rangers slugger tried to hop over the fence as the rangers took the field in celebration. It didn't go well. The struggle is real pic.twitter.com/6m9NNbkspg 
The real question, though: Is this worse than Prince's famous tumble in the 2013 ALCS?
